%U A116167 48089152118689474641229584727,66424317743191484432891678269
%N A116167 Numbers k such that k concatenated with k+1 gives the product of two numbers which differ by 7.
%C A116167 If k has d digits, the concatenation is k//k+1 = 10^d*k+k+1 = m*(m+7), therefore k//k-7 = 10^d*k+k-7 = (m-1)*(m+8), so there is a large overlap with A116114. - _R. J. Mathar_, May 22 2026
%e A116167 72757727//72757728 = 85298137 * 85298144, where // denotes concatenation.
